In this update:
[1] Rabies, rat, child - Russia (Kalmykia)
[2] Rabies, animal - Russia (Samara Region)
[3] Rabies human, animal - Ukraine (Zaporozhye)
[4] Rabies, human - Georgia
[5] Rabies, human, animal - Kyrgyzstan (Osh)
******
[1] Rabies, rat, child - Russia (Kalmykia)
Date: Wed 8 Aug 2007
Source: Regnum News Agency [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/868103.html>

According to Franzusova, head of Rospotrebnadzor [the Federal Service for
Monitoring Consumer Rights and Human Welfare] a 6 year old girl was bitten
by a rat in the grounds of a kindergarten on 2 Aug 2007. Investigations,
which have been carried by the city veterinary bacteriological laboratory,
have detected rabies in the animal. The rat had bitten the girl in a room
of the kindergarten on her return from a walk.
As a result, concern has been expressed about the unsatisfactory
performance of the municipal services regarding the control of rodents in
multistorey buildings and mismanagement by the authorities responsible for
the care of children in kindergarten. The injured child has been vaccinated
and is now under medical supervision. Rodent control measures are under way.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-rus@promedmail.org
[This report is difficult to evaluate. Rodents are not normally considered
vectors of rabies virus. - Mod.CP
The Republic of Kalmykia, on the north western shore of the Caspian Sea,
can be located on the map at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/russiaaddivisions.jpg>. -
CopyEd.MJ]
