[2] Rabies, animal - Russia (Samara Region)
Date: Wed 8 Aug 2007
Source: Regnum News Agency [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/867985.html>

As of 5 Aug 2007, 123 cases of rabies among animals have been recorded in
the Samara Region, according to the local management of Rospotrebnadzor in
the region. The numbers of cases of rabies among animals are significant in
23 areas of the Samara Region. A total of 227 people have been exposed to
animals with clinically and laboratory confirmed rabies.
The territory of the Samara Region is located in a natural focus of fox
rabies. The epizootic situation with regard to animal rabies continues to
be regarded as serious. In 2006, inadequate control of rabies was apparent
in 18 administrative districts where cases of rabies had been recorded
among wild, domestic, and agricultural animals. In the current year [2007],
there has been a marked deterioration in the epizootic situation with
regard to rabies. The largest number of cases has been registered in the
Borsky, Kinell-Cherkassky, and Kinelsky districts. Of the rabid animals, 45
per cent were dogs and 40 per cent were foxes.
--
