[3] Rabies human, animal - Ukraine (Zaporozhye)
Date: Thu 9 Aug 2007
Source: 24.ua News Agency [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://24.ua/news/society/10048/>

So far his year [2007], 3 children have died from rabies in the Zaporozhye
Region. The main vector of disease, according to experts is the fox. About
10 cases of rabies among pets have been registered this year [2007] in the
Zaporozhye Region, among them cows, dogs, and cats. All of them have been
destroyed.
[byline: Ludmila Krasilnikova]
--
communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-rus@promedmail.org
[Zaporozhye Region (Zaporizhia Oblast) in southern Ukraine can be located
on the map at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ukraine#Administrative_division>. - CopyEd.MJ]
******
[4] Rabies, human - Georgia
Date Tue 7 Aug 2007
Source: Regnum News Agency, IA Caucasus Press report [in Russian, trans.
Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.regnum.ru/news/867258.html>

In the 1st half of 2007, 7 people died of rabies in Georgia, stated Paata
Imnnadze, the director of the National Center for the Control of Diseases
and Public Health. All cases had a fatal outcome due to delayed referral
for treatment. A total of 18 222 persons have sought treatment in
connection with animal bites and of these, 12 755 have received anti-rabies
treatment. In the previous year [2006], 24 815 persons sought treatment and
18 270 received it.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-rus@promedmail.org
[A map of Georgia is available at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/georgia.pdf>. - CopyEd.MJ]
******
[5] Rabies, human, animal - Kyrgyzstan (Osh)
Date: Wed 8 Aug 2007
Source: Press-UZ News Agency News Agency [in Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
<http://www.press-uz.info/ru/content.scm?topic2803*contentId=98424>

The coordinator of the Southern Regional State Veterinary Science for the
Osh Region, Kanybek Begiev, has reviewed the epizootic situations in the
region. During the 1st half of 2007, 3 human deaths and 41 cases of rabies
among animals were reported in the Region.
The assistant governor of the Osh Region, Bolot Burguev, has instructed the
heads of medical establishments and veterinary services to undertake all
measures necessary for eliminating the epizootic of virus infection.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed-rus@promedmail.org
[Osh Region (Oblast) in southern Kyrgyzstan can be located on the map at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kyrgyzstan_pol_05.jpg>. -
CopyEd.MJ
Activation of the natural foci of rabies in Russia as a result of warm
winter weather has resulted in spread of rabies among pets and wildlife and
raised the risk of rabies for people. Failure to vaccinate pets and delayed
recourse of those bitten for post-exposure treatment have contributed to
this situation. It should be noted that the vaccination of pets against
rabies in Russia is mandatory. - Mod.NP]
